SIMPLE: spinning
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spinning
<hw>Spin"ning</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Spin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spinning gland</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>one of
the glands which form the material for spinning the silk of silkworms
and other larvae.</cd> -- <col><b>Spinning house</b></col>, <cd>formerly
a common name for a house of correction in England, the women confined
therein being employed in spinning.</cd> -- <col><b>Spinning
jenny</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>an engine or machine for
spinning wool or cotton, by means of a large number of spindles
revolving simultaneously.</cd> -- <col><b>Spinning mite</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the red spider.</cd> -- <col><b>Spinning
wheel</b></col>, <cd>a machine for spinning yarn or thread, in which a
wheel drives a single spindle, and is itself driven by the hand, or by
the foot acting on a treadle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spinny</ent>⟦br⟧
